President Biden visited the National Counterterrorism Center in Virginia to thank the intelligence professionals for their work in keeping the country safe. He expressed his gratitude and emphasized the importance of their efforts in protecting the American people. He also highlighted the need for intelligence agencies to remain free from political pressure and partisan interference. President Biden discussed the evolving nature of security threats, including cyber threats and disinformation, and the importance of staying ahead of these challenges. He emphasized the need for cooperation with allies and partners, particularly in addressing climate change. President Biden also touched on the issue of anomalous health incidents affecting intelligence officers and pledged to prioritize the safety and well-being of those working in the intelligence community. He concluded by expressing his appreciation for the intelligence professionals and acknowledging the vital role they play in safeguarding the nation.